snippet.title: Congo's Caper (SNES) Playthrough - NintendoComplete
snippet.description:
A complete playthrough of Data East's 1993 Super NES platformer, Congo's Caper.

This was originally meant to be a followup to Joe & Mac, and the influences are pretty clear, even down to the Joe statue in the bonus levels that you club to get diamonds.   It's a lot of fun, and plays extremely smoothly. Give it a go if you haven't!
__________
No cheats were used during the recording of this video.
